2026-04-19 | Maximum Distance Between Valid Pairs

Question
Return maximum distance among all valid pairs.
	Approach
1.	Use two pointers:
		i = 0 (nums1)  
		j = 0 (nums2)  
2.	Traverse:
		while i < n1 and j < n2:
3.	If nums1[i] ≤ nums2[j]:
		valid pair → update answer  
		move j forward (increase distance)  
4.	Else:
		move i forward (need smaller nums1[i])  
5.	Keep track of max distance  
	Time Complexity
	O(n + m)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maxDistance(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        int n1 = nums1.size(), n2 = nums2.size();
        int ans = 0;
        while(i < n1 && j < n2){
            if(nums1[i] <= nums2[j]){
                ans = max(ans, j - i);
                j++;
            } else {
                i++;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Because arrays are **non-increasing**:
- moving j forward reduces nums2[j]  
- moving i forward reduces nums1[i]  
This monotonic behavior allows efficient **two-pointer traversal** instead of brute force.
